    <p class="text-gray-300">The average DP can be computed as the total cardinality divided by  <span class="math">2^h</span> , the number of possible keys, and  <span class="math">2^{n-1}</span> , the number of pairs with input difference a.</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300"><strong>Theorem 10</strong> The distribution of the total cardinality of a differential over a random block cipher is very close to a normal distribution with mean  <span class="math">\\mu(N_{\\rm tot}) = 2^{h-1}</span>  and standard deviation  <span class="math">\\sigma(N_{\\rm tot}) = \\sqrt{2^h 2^{-1}} = 2^{(h-1)/2}</span> .</p>

